      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SACRED INFERNO (1) broke his maiden last start at Gundagai when lengthening nicely in the lane to score with a bit in reserve. Draws the A1 can go right on with the job now. STURTY (8) turned in a decent effort last start to finish third over 1600m at Goulburn. Looks better placed back to 1400m and should be at peak fitness now. Gets his chance to break a long run of outs. Sure to prove tough to beat again with that win now under his belt. SAVAHAY (5) was given a short break after finishing fourth over 1200m at Wagga. Kept ticking over with a subsequent trial at Wagga Riverside. Rates well and looks a winning hope. SEASMOKE (3) has been in good form, scoring three back at this track then placing in her last two. Likely to be about the money again.",
